      "id": 56872,
      "category": "researcher",
      "content": "###Summary\nWhen a user changes their email, they can receive a verification code in the changed email. This verification code will be used when changing your email.\n\nbut, drive2.ru can reuse a corrupted verification code because the previously issued email change verification code does not expire when a new email change verification code is issued due to improper session expiration.\n\n###Risk\nThere are currently no immediate security risks. However, according to OWASP, old sessions must expire when requesting a new session, so it may be best security practice to expire old unused verification codes when issuing a new verification code.",
